These readings provide very practical insights into the ways that data transformation can ‚Äòtorture the data until it confesses‚Äô as well as how we can use data transformation to generate new ways of seeing our data and, consequently, new ways of understanding it. You should be coming out of these readings with a clearer understanding of why there‚Äôs rarely a ‚Äòright‚Äô or ‚Äòwrong‚Äô approach to a real-world data set, but there are ‚Äòbetter‚Äô and ‚Äòworse‚Äô approaches. These readings are predominantly non-academic so they should (I hope) be fairly accessible and quick to read despite the potential dryness of the topics.
